"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60878","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2014-06-17","<p>Information on apprenticeship starts and achievements by gender, ethnicity and learners with learning difficulties and/or disabilities (LLDD) is published by academic year in supplementary tables to a Statistical First Release (SFR).</p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/statistical-data-sets/fe-data-library-apprenticeships--2" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/statistical-data-sets/fe-data-library-apprenticeships--2</a></p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/298401/apprenticeships-starts-by-geography-learner-demographics-and-sector-subject-area.xls" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/298401/apprenticeships-starts-by-geography-learner-demographics-and-sector-subject-area.xls</a></p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/296345/apprenticeship-achievements-by-geography-learner-demographics-and-sector-subject-area.xlsm" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/296345/apprenticeship-achievements-by-geography-learner-demographics-and-sector-subject-area.xlsm</a></p>","West Suffolk","Matthew Hancock",,"2014-06-17T13:05:43.6399387Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60878/answer","Biography information for Matt Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60878/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60878/answer",,,,,,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2014-06-10","Apprentices","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, what proportion of those (a) starting and (b) completing an apprenticeship in England since May 2010 were (i) female, (ii) registered disabled and (iii) from an ethnic minority background.","false","Biography information for Mrs Sharon Hodgson","Washington and Sunderland West","Mrs Sharon Hodgson","199999"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60879","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2014-06-17","<p>The Government supports a living wage and encourages businesses to pay it when it is affordable and not at the expense of jobs. However, decisions on what wages to set, above the national minimum wage, are for employers and workers.</p><p>The Government has not estimated the breakdown of workers earning between the National Minimum Wage and the Living Wage by ethnicity.</p><p>The Government's main policy lever in addressing low pay is the National Minimum Wage (NMW). Using the Labour Force Survey, in 2013, 8.3% of the ‘ethnic minority' group (see footnote) were in jobs that paid at or below the NMW while overall 7.8% of the jobs in the economy paid at or below the NMW. This is as set out in the Low Pay Commission's 2014 Report, Figure 2.6.</p><p>We are absolutely clear that anyone from whatever background who is entitled to be paid the minimum wage should receive it. HMRC investigates every complaint made through the free and confidential Pay and Work Rights Helpline. Since 1 October 2013, employers who fail to pay the National Minimum Wage (NMW) will be publicly named and shamed under revamped criteria announced in August 2013 to make it easier to clamp down on rogue businesses. This is on top of financial penalties which employers already face if they fail to pay NMW.</p><p>Footnote:</p><p>The definition of ‘ethnic-minority' group is as defined in the Labour Force Survey (LFS)</p><p>Also please note that the LFS overstates the number of Minimum Wage jobs and workers when compared to the Annual Survey of Hours and Earnings (ASHE) dataset.</p>","Cardiff Central","Jenny Willott",,"2014-06-17T16:54:07.1081839Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60879/answer","Biography information for Jenny Willott","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60879/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60879/answer",,,,,,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2014-06-10","Minimum Wage: Ethnic Groups","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, what estimate he has made of the ethnic breakdown of workers earning between the National Minimum Wage and the Living Wage.","false","Biography information for Mrs Sharon Hodgson","Washington and Sunderland West","Mrs Sharon Hodgson","199996"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60880","Cabinet Office","false","2014-06-18","<p>The information requested falls within the responsibility of the UK Statistics Authority. I have asked the Authority to reply.</p><p> </p>","Ruislip, Northwood and Pinner","Mr Nick Hurd",,"2014-06-18T12:16:37.127",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60880/answer","Biography information for Mr Nick Hurd","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60880/answer","PQ 199997.pdf","PQ 199997.pdf","ONS Letter to Member","ONS Letter to Member","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60880/answer",,,,,,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2014-06-10","Conditions of Employment: Ethnic Groups","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, what estimate he has made of the ethnic breakdown of workers on zero hour contracts.","false","Biography information for Mrs Sharon Hodgson","Washington and Sunderland West","Mrs Sharon Hodgson","199997"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60881","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2014-06-17","<p>Higher education institutions (HEIs) are independent, autonomous bodies and are entirely responsible for the recruitment, promotion and retention of their staff. Universities, like other employers, are subject to the requirements of the Equality Act 2010 and must ensure they do not discriminate in their recruitment practices. Universities are also required to meet the Public Sector Equality Duty and take a proactive approach to advancing equality of opportunity.</p><p>I understand that employer and employee representative organisations are taking action to address issues of equality in the higher education sector workforce. The Higher Education Funding Council for England (HEFCE) through the Equality Challenge Unit and in other ways, works with the higher education (HE) sector to support activities to address issues of representation both in the HE workforce and student population.</p>","Havant","Mr David Willetts",,"2014-06-17T13:13:57.6698108Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60881/answer","Biography information for Lord Willetts","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60881/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60881/answer",,,,,,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2014-06-10","Teachers: Ethnic Groups","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, what steps his Department has taken to increase the number of black and minority ethnic professors teaching in public universities.","false","Biography information for Mrs Sharon Hodgson","Washington and Sunderland West","Mrs Sharon Hodgson","199998"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60882","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2014-06-17","<p>I refer the Hon. Member to the answer by my Rt. Hon. Friend the Minister for the Cabinet Office (Francis Maude) on 16 June 2014, Official Report, column 434W.</p>","Cardiff Central","Jenny Willott",,"2014-06-17T16:48:56.077798Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60882/answer","Biography information for Jenny Willott","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60882/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60882/answer",,,,,,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2014-06-10","Equality","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, what consideration his Department gives to the diversity policies and records of businesses or other organisations when considering their bid for commercial contracts or grants.","false","Biography information for Mrs Sharon Hodgson","Washington and Sunderland West","Mrs Sharon Hodgson","199939"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60883","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2014-06-17","<p>I refer the Hon. Member to the answer by my Rt. Hon. Friend the Minister for the Cabinet Office (Francis Maude) on 16 June 2014, Official Report, column 434W.</p>","Cardiff Central","Jenny Willott",,"2014-06-17T16:51:18.9214955Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60883/answer","Biography information for Jenny Willott","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60883/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60883/answer",,,,,,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2014-06-10","Equality","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, what targets his Department has for increasing diversity; and what progress has been made on meeting those targets in the last year.","false","Biography information for Mrs Sharon Hodgson","Washington and Sunderland West","Mrs Sharon Hodgson","199918"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60884","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2014-06-17","<p>I refer the hon. Member to the answergiven by my Rt. Hon. Friend the Minister for the Cabinet Office (Francis Maude) on 16 June 2014, Official Report, column 433W.</p>","Cardiff Central","Jenny Willott","199896","2014-06-17T16:56:40.1815323Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60884/answer","Biography information for Jenny Willott","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60884/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60884/answer",,,,,,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2014-06-10","Disciplinary Proceedings","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, what proportion of staff within his Department who have been subject to formal disciplinary proceedings in each of the last five financial years classed themselves as white British.","false","Biography information for Mrs Sharon Hodgson","Washington and Sunderland West","Mrs Sharon Hodgson","199875"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60885","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2014-06-17","<p>I refer the hon. Member to the answergiven by my Rt. Hon. Friend the Minister for the Cabinet Office (Francis Maude) on 16 June 2014, Official Report, column 433W.</p>","Cardiff Central","Jenny Willott","199875","2014-06-17T16:56:40.1094208Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60885/answer","Biography information for Jenny Willott","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60885/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60885/answer",,,,,,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2014-06-10","Disciplinary Proceedings","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, what proportion of staff within his Department who have been dismissed following formal disciplinary proceedings in each of the last five financial years classed themselves as white British.","false","Biography information for Mrs Sharon Hodgson","Washington and Sunderland West","Mrs Sharon Hodgson","199896"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60886","Cabinet Office","false","2014-06-17","<p>I refer the hon. Member to the answer I gave to her on Monday 16 June 2014 (Official Report) Column Ref: 434W.</p><p> </p>","Horsham","Mr Francis Maude",,"2014-06-17T16:27:30.1116991Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60886/answer","Biography information for Lord Maude of Horsham","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60886/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60886/answer",,,,,,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2014-06-10","Civil Servants: Equal Opportunities","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, when he plans to publish a new diversity strategy for the Civil Service.","false","Biography information for Mrs Sharon Hodgson","Washington and Sunderland West","Mrs Sharon Hodgson","199873"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60887","Cabinet Office","false","2014-06-16","<p>The Prime Minister's Office and the Deputy Prime Minister's Office are integral parts of the Cabinet Office.</p><p>Declaration of ethnicity for staff is voluntary and it is therefore not possible to provide the information requested.</p><p> </p>","Horsham","Mr Francis Maude","199877 ; 199892 ; 199914","2014-06-16T16:36:16.6572159Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60887/answer","Biography information for Lord Maude of Horsham","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60887/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60887/answer",,,,,,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2014-06-10","Disciplinary Proceedings","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, what proportion of staff within his Department who have been dismissed following formal disciplinary proceedings in each of the last five financial years classed themselves as white British.","false","Biography information for Mrs Sharon Hodgson","Washington and Sunderland West","Mrs Sharon Hodgson","199898"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60888","Cabinet Office","false","2014-06-16","<p>The Prime Minister's Office and the Deputy Prime Ministers Office are an integral part of the Cabinet Office.</p><p>This Government procures on the basis of value for money. Departments and the Crown Commercial Service will ensure that social, economic and sustainability issues are considered in procurement projects and that specifications, terms and conditions and evaluation criteria are developed to ensure that the relevant issues are addressed as appropriate for the subject matter of the requirements.</p><p> </p>","Horsham","Mr Francis Maude","199956","2014-06-16T16:31:06.8495988Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60888/answer","Biography information for Lord Maude of Horsham","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60888/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60888/answer",,,,,,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2014-06-10","Equality","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, what consideration his Department gives to the diversity policies and records of businesses or other organisations when considering their bid for commercial contracts or grants.","false","Biography information for Mrs Sharon Hodgson","Washington and Sunderland West","Mrs Sharon Hodgson","199941"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60889","Cabinet Office","false","2014-06-16","<p>To win the global race we need the best civil servants regardless of their background so we must recruit, retain and promote on the basis of merit. We want to see more talented people, whatever their background, reach the very top roles.<br> <br> There has been for many years a majority of women in the Civil Service but this was not reflected into the Senior Civil Service.</p><p> </p><p>Although there has been a small increase in the proportion of women in the Senior Civil Service since 2010, and in the proportion of civil servants who declare that they are from an ethnic minority background, there is still much to do. <br> <br> We know that for too long talent management in the Civil Service has been weak. That's why I have commissioned research to examine the blockages preventing women from reaching the most senior levels of the Civil Service.<br> <br> A plan to address these issues will be published this summer.</p><p> </p><p> </p>","Horsham","Mr Francis Maude","199924 ; 199935","2014-06-16T16:46:34.9377509Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60889/answer","Biography information for Lord Maude of Horsham","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60889/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60889/answer",,,,,,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2014-06-10","Equality","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, what targets his Department has for increasing diversity; and what progress has been made on meeting those targets in the last year.","false","Biography information for Mrs Sharon Hodgson","Washington and Sunderland West","Mrs Sharon Hodgson","199920"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60890","Cabinet Office","false","2014-06-16","<p>The Prime Minister's Office and the Deputy Prime Minister's Office are integral parts of the Cabinet Office.</p><p>Declaration of ethnicity for staff is voluntary and it is therefore not possible to provide the information requested.</p><p> </p>","Horsham","Mr Francis Maude","199892 ; 199898 ; 199914","2014-06-16T16:36:16.4768884Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60890/answer","Biography information for Lord Maude of Horsham","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60890/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60890/answer",,,,,,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2014-06-10","Disciplinary Proceedings","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, what proportion of staff within his Department who have been subject to formal disciplinary proceedings in each of the last five financial years classed themselves as white British.","false","Biography information for Mrs Sharon Hodgson","Washington and Sunderland West","Mrs Sharon Hodgson","199877"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60891","HM Treasury","false","2014-06-23","<p>I refer the hon. Member to the answer given to her on 16 June 2014, <em>Official Report</em>, column 433W, by the Minister for the Cabinet Office.</p>","South Northamptonshire","Andrea Leadsom","199894","2014-06-23T16:08:16.6538796Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60891/answer","Biography information for Andrea Leadsom","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60891/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60891/answer",,,,,,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2014-06-10","Disciplinary Proceedings","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what proportion of staff within his Department who have been dismissed following formal disciplinary proceedings in each of the last five financial years classed themselves as white British.","false","Biography information for Mrs Sharon Hodgson","Washington and Sunderland West","Mrs Sharon Hodgson","199916"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60892","HM Treasury","false","2014-06-23","<p>I refer the hon. Member to the answer given to her on 16 June 2014, <em>Official Report</em>, column 433W, by the Minister for the Cabinet Office.</p>","South Northamptonshire","Andrea Leadsom","199916","2014-06-23T16:08:16.7476115Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60892/answer","Biography information for Andrea Leadsom","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60892/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60892/answer",,,,,,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2014-06-10","Disciplinary Proceedings","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what proportion of staff within his Department who have been subject to formal disciplinary proceedings in each of the last five financial years classed themselves as white British.","false","Biography information for Mrs Sharon Hodgson","Washington and Sunderland West","Mrs Sharon Hodgson","199894"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60893","HM Treasury","false","2014-06-17","<p><strong>In common with other government departments the Treasury has diversity targets for its workforce (gender, ethnicity and disability), monitors progress and implements diversity initiatives where appropriate. </strong></p><p> </p><p><strong>HM Treasury diversity targets for its Senior Civil Service (SCS) </strong></p><table><tbody><tr><td><p><strong>Group</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>Target</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>Women</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>42 %</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>BME</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>5% </strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>Disability</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>5% </strong></p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><p><strong>HM Treasury's diversity targets for its employees below the SCS</strong></p><table><tbody><tr><td><p><strong>Group</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>Target</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>Women Range E</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>50% </strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>Women Range D</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>50% </strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>BME Range E</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>14%</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>BME Range D</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>18%</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>Disability Range E</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>6%</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>Disability Range D</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>8%</strong></p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><p> </p><p><strong>On progress against the targets the Treasury publishes information on the proportion of its employees by gender, ethnicity and disability by each Civil Service pay scale. The most recent information, March 2013, is in HM Treasury's <em>Annual Report and Accounts 2012-13</em>, page 43, available on the Treasury's external website. </strong></p><p> </p><p> </p><p><strong>The March 2014 data will be published in the <em>Annual Report and Accounts</em> 2014 in due course</strong></p>","South Northamptonshire","Andrea Leadsom",,"2014-06-17T15:05:03.955967Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60893/answer","Biography information for Andrea Leadsom","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60893/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60893/answer",,,,,,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2014-06-10","Equal Opportunities","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what targets his Department has for increasing diversity; and what progress has been made on meeting those targets in the last year.","false","Biography information for Mrs Sharon Hodgson","Washington and Sunderland West","Mrs Sharon Hodgson","199937"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60894","HM Treasury","false","2014-06-17","<p><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/In_July" target="_blank">In July</a>In July 2013 HM Treasury's procurement functions transferred to the Crown Commercial Service (CCS—formerly the Government Procurement Service, GPS). HM Treasury decides selection criteria and weightings for procurements based on advice from CCS.</p><p> </p><p>The selection criteria and weightings in the procurement procedures used by CCS are not fixed, but vary from project to project. UKpublic procurement policy is to award contracts on the basis of value for money, which means the optimum combination of cost and quality over the lifetime of the project. Public sector procurers are required to assess value for money from the perspective of the contracting authority using criteria linked to the subject matter of the contract, including compliance with the published specification.</p><p> </p><p>Diversity policies and records of businesses can be taken into account at tender evaluation stage if they relate directly to the subject matter of a contract from the point of view of the contracting authority.</p><p> </p><p>Treasury's procurements are evaluated against response guidance provided to bidders as part of Invitations to Tender (ITT) or Requests for Quotes (RFQ). Since January 2011, central Government Departments have been required to publish on Contracts Finder information on the tenders issued and contracts they award with a value over £10,000 (excluding VAT):</p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/contracts-finder" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/contracts-finder</a></p><p> </p><p>Selection criteria and weightings applied in procurements form part of the information published.</p>","South Northamptonshire","Andrea Leadsom",,"2014-06-17T15:07:42.147",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60894/answer","Biography information for Andrea Leadsom","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60894/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60894/answer",,,,,,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2014-06-10","Equality","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what consideration his Department gives to the diversity policies and records of businesses or other organisations when considering their bid for commercial contracts or grants.","false","Biography information for Mrs Sharon Hodgson","Washington and Sunderland West","Mrs Sharon Hodgson","199958"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60895","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2014-07-01","<p> </p><p>It is not possible to provide definitive or meaningful percentages, as (a) not all staff declare their ethnicity, (b) due to the manner in which white ethnicity data is self-reported by staff , and (c) the sample sizes are so small as to be statistically misleading when comparing years.</p><p> </p>","Great Yarmouth","Brandon Lewis","199878","2014-07-01T13:55:54.1346711Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60895/answer","Biography information for Brandon Lewis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60895/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60895/answer",,,,,,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2014-06-10","Disciplinary Proceedings","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, what proportion of staff within his Department who have been dismissed following formal disciplinary proceedings in each of the last five financial years classed themselves as white British.","false","Biography information for Mrs Sharon Hodgson","Washington and Sunderland West","Mrs Sharon Hodgson","199899"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60896","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2014-06-17","<p> </p><p>This Government procures on the basis of value for money. Departments and the Crown Commercial Service will ensure that social, economic and sustainability issues are considered in procurement projects and that specifications, terms and conditions and evaluation criteria are developed to ensure that the relevant issues are addressed as appropriate for the subject matter of the requirements.</p><p> </p><p>As outlined in the Written Ministerial Statement of 6 September 2013, <em>Official Report</em>, Column 33WS, on the Government response to the public sector equality duty review, there is clear evidence of equality and diversity policies going too far in the other direction, by imposing unreasonable and expensive burdens on organisations bidding for public sector contracts. The Government has committed to reducing procurement gold-plating by the public sector.</p><p> </p>","Great Yarmouth","Brandon Lewis",,"2014-06-17T15:54:44.9099871Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60896/answer","Biography information for Brandon Lewis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60896/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60896/answer",,,,,,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2014-06-10","Equal Opportunities","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, what consideration his Department gives to the diversity policies and records of businesses or other organisations when considering their bid for commercial contracts or grants.","false","Biography information for Mrs Sharon Hodgson","Washington and Sunderland West","Mrs Sharon Hodgson","199942"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60897","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2014-07-01","<p> </p><p>It is not possible to provide definitive or meaningful percentages, as (a) not all staff declare their ethnicity, (b) due to the manner in which white ethnicity data is self-reported by staff , and (c) the sample sizes are so small as to be statistically misleading when comparing years.</p><p> </p>","Great Yarmouth","Brandon Lewis","199899","2014-07-01T13:55:54.0721261Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60897/answer","Biography information for Brandon Lewis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60897/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60897/answer",,,,,,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2014-06-10","Disciplinary Proceedings","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, what proportion of staff within his Department who have been subject to formal disciplinary proceedings in each of the last five financial years classed themselves as white British.","false","Biography information for Mrs Sharon Hodgson","Washington and Sunderland West","Mrs Sharon Hodgson","199878"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60898","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2014-06-23","<p> </p><p>I refer the hon. Member to the answer given by the Minister for the Cabinet Office and Paymaster General, the right hon. Member for Horsham (Francis Maude) on 16 June, <em>Official Report</em>, Column 434W.</p><p> </p>","Great Yarmouth","Brandon Lewis",,"2014-06-23T14:09:47.5027306Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60898/answer","Biography information for Brandon Lewis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60898/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60898/answer",,,,,,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2014-06-10","Equality","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, what targets his Department has for increasing diversity; and what progress has been made on meeting those targets in the last year.","false","Biography information for Mrs Sharon Hodgson","Washington and Sunderland West","Mrs Sharon Hodgson","199921"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60899","Department for Culture Media and Sport","false","2014-06-17","<p>The Department for Culture, Media and Sport, which includes the Government Equalities Office, has no specific targets for increasing employeediversity. DCMS publishes its employee diversity information on data.gov.uk annually. The most recent diversity information can be found at the following link</p><p> </p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/237397/DCMS_Equality_Workforce_Data_2012-2013.csv/preview" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/237397/DCMS_Equality_Workforce_Data_2012-2013.csv/preview</a></p>","Maidstone and The Weald","Mrs Helen Grant",,"2014-06-17T09:59:10.1171837Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60899/answer","Biography information for Mrs Helen Grant","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60899/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60899/answer",,,,,,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2014-06-10","Equality","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, what targets his Department has for increasing diversity; and what progress has been made on meeting those targets in the last year.","false","Biography information for Mrs Sharon Hodgson","Washington and Sunderland West","Mrs Sharon Hodgson","199922"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60900","Department for Culture Media and Sport","false","2014-06-17","<p>The table shows the proportion of staff, within the Department for Culture, Media and Sport, who have been subject to formal disciplinary proceedings in each of the last five financial years and who have declared themselves as white British.</p><table><tbody><tr><td><p>Year</p></td><td><p><strong>Percentage of DCMS headcount who have been subject to disciplinary proceedings</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>Proportion of staff subject to disciplinary proceedings who declared themselves as white British</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>Proportion of staff subject to disciplinary proceedings who declared their nationality as British but ethnicity is undeclared</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p>1 April 2009 – 31 March 2010</p></td><td><p>0.2%</p></td><td><p>100%</p></td><td><p>0%</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>1 April 2010 – 31 March 2011</p></td><td><p>0.7%</p></td><td><p>67%</p></td><td><p>33%</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>1 April 2011 – 31 March 2012</p></td><td><p>0.4%</p></td><td><p>50%</p></td><td><p>50%</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>1 April 2012 – 31 March 2013</p></td><td><p>0.3%</p></td><td><p>100%</p></td><td><p>0%</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>1 April 2013 – 31 March 2014</p></td><td><p>0.8%</p></td><td><p>67%</p></td><td><p>33%</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><p>The figures as they relate to the period from September 2012 include the Government Equalities Office, which joined the Department in that month as part of a machinery of Government move. Before September 2012, the Government Equalities Office was part of the Home Office and the information requested for this period is not available.</p><p> </p>","Maidstone and The Weald","Mrs Helen Grant",,"2014-06-17T13:48:42.5141165Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60900/answer","Biography information for Mrs Helen Grant","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60900/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60900/answer",,,,,,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2014-06-10","Disciplinary Proceedings","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, what proportion of staff within his Department who have been subject to formal disciplinary proceedings in each of the last five financial years classed themselves as white British.","false","Biography information for Mrs Sharon Hodgson","Washington and Sunderland West","Mrs Sharon Hodgson","199879"
