"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60902","Department for Culture Media and Sport","false","2014-06-17","<p>The table shows the proportion of staff within the Department for Culture, media and Sport who have been dismissed following formal disciplinary proceedings in each of the last five financial years and declared themselves as white British.</p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p>Year</p></td><td><p><strong>Percentage of DCMS headcount who have been dismissed</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>Proportion of staff dismissed following formal disciplinary proceedings who declared themselves as white British</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>Proportion of staff subject to disciplinary proceedings who declared their nationality as British but ethnicity is undeclared</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p>1 April 2009 – 31 March 2010</p></td><td><p>0%</p></td><td><p>-</p></td><td><p>-</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>1 April 2010 – 31 March 2011</p></td><td><p>0%</p></td><td><p>-</p></td><td><p>-</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>1 April 2011 – 31 March 2012</p></td><td><p>0.2%</p></td><td><p>100%</p></td><td><p>0%</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>1 April 2012 – 31 March 2013</p></td><td><p>0%</p></td><td><p>-</p></td><td><p>-</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>1 April 2013 – 31 March 2014</p></td><td><p>0%</p></td><td><p>-</p></td><td><p>-</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><p>The figures as they relate to the period from September 2012 include the Government Equalities Office, which joined the Department in that month as part of a machinery of Government move. Before September 2012, the Government Equalities Office was part of the Home Office and the information requested for this period is not available.</p>","Maidstone and The Weald","Mrs Helen Grant",,"2014-06-17T13:52:30.5167257Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60902/answer","Biography information for Mrs Helen Grant","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60902/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60902/answer",,,,,,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2014-06-10","Disciplinary Proceedings","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, what proportion of staff within his Department who have been dismissed following formal disciplinary proceedings in each of the last five financial years classed themselves as white British.","false","Biography information for Mrs Sharon Hodgson","Washington and Sunderland West","Mrs Sharon Hodgson","199900"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60903","Ministry of Defence","false","2014-06-18","<p>The information requested is shown in the tables below.<br><br>Proportion of Ministry of Defence Civil Servant disciplinary cases in which subject was White British<br><br>2009/10 84.7%<br>2010/11 83.7%<br>2011/12 82.3%<br>2012/13 76.8%<br>2013/14 78.1%<br><br>Proportion of Ministry of Defence Civil Servant conduct dismissal cases in which subject was White British.<br><br>2009/10 77.2%<br>2010/11 86.5%<br>2011/12 68.9%<br>2012/13 81.1%<br>2013/14 72.6%</p>","Broxtowe","Anna Soubry","199880","2014-06-18T16:38:26.5822066Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60903/answer","Biography information for Anna Soubry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60903/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60903/answer",,,,,,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2014-06-10","Disciplinary Proceedings","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what proportion of staff within his Department who have been dismissed following formal disciplinary proceedings in each of the last five financial years classed themselves as white British.","false","Biography information for Mrs Sharon Hodgson","Washington and Sunderland West","Mrs Sharon Hodgson","199901"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60904","Ministry of Defence","false","2014-06-17","<p> </p><p>The Ministry of Defence will consider the diversity policies and records of businesses or other organisations where they are relevant and proportionate to the subject matter of the contract, and seeking best value for money in procurement.</p><p> </p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne",,"2014-06-17T16:00:59.770701Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60904/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60904/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60904/answer",,,,,,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2014-06-10","Equality","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what consideration his Department gives to the diversity policies and records of businesses or other organisations when considering their bid for commercial contracts or grants.","false","Biography information for Mrs Sharon Hodgson","Washington and Sunderland West","Mrs Sharon Hodgson","199944"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60905","Ministry of Defence","false","2014-06-18","<p>The information requested is shown in the tables below.<br><br>Proportion of Ministry of Defence Civil Servant disciplinary cases in which subject was White British<br><br>2009/10 84.7%<br>2010/11 83.7%<br>2011/12 82.3%<br>2012/13 76.8%<br>2013/14 78.1%<br><br>Proportion of Ministry of Defence Civil Servant conduct dismissal cases in which subject was White British.<br><br>2009/10 77.2%<br>2010/11 86.5%<br>2011/12 68.9%<br>2012/13 81.1%<br>2013/14 72.6%</p>","Broxtowe","Anna Soubry","199901","2014-06-18T16:38:26.3947127Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60905/answer","Biography information for Anna Soubry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60905/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60905/answer",,,,,,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2014-06-10","Disciplinary Proceedings","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what proportion of staff within his Department who have been subject to formal disciplinary proceedings in each of the last five financial years classed themselves as white British.","false","Biography information for Mrs Sharon Hodgson","Washington and Sunderland West","Mrs Sharon Hodgson","199880"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60906","Ministry of Defence","false","2014-06-18","<p>The Ministry of Defence (MOD) does not have targets for increasing diversity. <br><br>In 2012 the MOD published its Strategic Equality Objectives in accordance with the statutory requirements flowing from the Equality Act 2010 to promote equality. These objectives, including the advancement of equality of opportunity, were endorsed by the Defence Board to reflect the fact that the duty to promote equality sits squarely at the top of the Department.<br><br>In September 2013, the Permanent Secretary and Chief of the Defence Staff announced the establishment of a Defence Diversity and Inclusion Programme, with the aim of making a tangible and meaningful change in the MOD's approach to diversity and diversity outcomes. <br><br>The primary aim of the programme is to make the workforce more representative of society at all levels, and metrics will be used to measure success.<br><br>The MOD publishes a biannual breakdown of diversity statistics which contains analysis of all diversity categories for both civilian and Service Personnel. The most recent report, published on 29 May 2014, can be found at the following address: http://www.dasa.mod.uk/index.php/publications/personnel/combined/diversity-dashboard</p>","Broxtowe","Anna Soubry",,"2014-06-18T16:03:47.4387856Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60906/answer","Biography information for Anna Soubry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60906/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60906/answer",,,,,,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2014-06-10","Equality","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what targets his Department has for increasing diversity; and what progress has been made on meeting those targets in the last year.","false","Biography information for Mrs Sharon Hodgson","Washington and Sunderland West","Mrs Sharon Hodgson","199923"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60907","Deputy Prime Minister","false","2014-06-16","<p>I refer the hon. Member to the answer given by My Rt Hon Friend the Minister for the Cabinet Office today.</p>","Sheffield, Hallam","Mr Nick Clegg","199902","2014-06-16T16:51:48.1698217Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60907/answer","Biography information for Mr Nick Clegg","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60907/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60907/answer",,,,,,,,,"58","Deputy Prime Minister","Deputy Prime Minister","2014-06-10","Disciplinary Proceedings","1","House of Commons","To ask the Deputy Prime Minister, what proportion of staff within his Office who have been subject to formal disciplinary proceedings in each of the last five financial years classed themselves as white British.","false","Biography information for Mrs Sharon Hodgson","Washington and Sunderland West","Mrs Sharon Hodgson","199881"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60908","Cabinet Office","false","2014-06-16","<p>To win the global race we need the best civil servants regardless of their background so we must recruit, retain and promote on the basis of merit. We want to see more talented people, whatever their background, reach the very top roles.<br> <br> There has been for many years a majority of women in the Civil Service but this was not reflected into the Senior Civil Service.</p><p> </p><p>Although there has been a small increase in the proportion of women in the Senior Civil Service since 2010, and in the proportion of civil servants who declare that they are from an ethnic minority background, there is still much to do. <br> <br> We know that for too long talent management in the Civil Service has been weak. That's why I have commissioned research to examine the blockages preventing women from reaching the most senior levels of the Civil Service.<br> <br> A plan to address these issues will be published this summer.</p><p> </p><p> </p>","Horsham","Mr Francis Maude","199920 ; 199935","2014-06-16T16:46:35.0172951Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60908/answer","Biography information for Lord Maude of Horsham","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60908/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60908/answer",,,,,,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2014-06-10","Equality","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, what targets the Cabinet Office has for increasing diversity; and what progress has been made on meeting those targets in the last year.","false","Biography information for Mrs Sharon Hodgson","Washington and Sunderland West","Mrs Sharon Hodgson","199924"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60909","Deputy Prime Minister","false","2014-06-16","<p>I refer the hon. Member to the answer given by My Rt Hon Friend the Minister for the Cabinet Office today.</p>","Sheffield, Hallam","Mr Nick Clegg",,"2014-06-16T16:53:01.4418537Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60909/answer","Biography information for Mr Nick Clegg","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60909/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60909/answer",,,,,,,,,"58","Deputy Prime Minister","Deputy Prime Minister","2014-06-10","Equality","1","House of Commons","To ask the Deputy Prime Minister, what consideration his Office gives to the diversity policies and records of businesses or other organisations when considering their bid for commercial contracts or grants.","false","Biography information for Mrs Sharon Hodgson","Washington and Sunderland West","Mrs Sharon Hodgson","199945"
