"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60911","Department for Education","false","2014-06-17","<p>Our data does not record nationality; data held records only ethnicity.</p>","South West Norfolk","Elizabeth Truss",,"2014-06-17T16:50:42.9271086Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60911/answer","Biography information for Elizabeth Truss","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60911/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60911/answer",,,,,,,,,"60","Education","Education","2014-06-10","Disciplinary Proceedings","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, what proportion of staff within his Department who have been dismissed following formal disciplinary proceedings in each of the last five financial years classed themselves as white British.","false","Biography information for Mrs Sharon Hodgson","Washington and Sunderland West","Mrs Sharon Hodgson","199903"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60912","Department for Education","false","2014-06-17","<p>Because of the significant changes in the school funding system between financial years 2010-11 and 2013-14, it is not possible to provide meaningfully-comparable data on funding to individual schools in the two years. In addition, the amount of funding a school receives will change from year to year depending on the number of pupils registered at the school as well as the schools funding formula determined by the local authority, the arrangements for which were reformed in 2013-14 to comprise 12 nationally-consistent factors.</p>","Yeovil","Mr David Laws",,"2014-06-17T11:27:11.4687679Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60912/answer","Biography information for Mr David Laws","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60912/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60912/answer",,,,,,,,,"60","Education","Education","2014-06-10","Schools: North East","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, how many schools in (a) Washington and Sunderland West constituency, (b) the Sunderland local authority area and (c) the North East region are receiving less overall funding in 2013-14 than they did in 2010-11.","false","Biography information for Mrs Sharon Hodgson","Washington and Sunderland West","Mrs Sharon Hodgson","199864"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60913","Department for Education","false","2014-06-16","<p>On 18 December 2013, the Government announced capital allocations for universal infant free school meals for the 2014-2015 financial year. This included allocations of (a) £562,850 to Sunderland City Council and (b) £6.1 million to all local authorities in the North East region. We do not allocate funding at a constituency level.</p><p> </p><p>In addition, academies have received capital funding through the Academies Capital Maintenance Fund. This includes allocations of (a) £162,380 to academies within the Sunderland local authority area and (b) £311,608 to academies within the North East region. Across the country, £2.5 million has also been made available to multi-academy trusts.</p><p> </p><p>Of the capital funding that has been allocated to Sunderland, the authority has confirmed to the Department that 75% or more has been disbursed to specific projects to support universal infant free school meals. We do not hold information on the precise amount disbursed, and nor do we hold this data at a regional level.</p><p> </p>","Yeovil","Mr David Laws",,"2014-06-16T14:39:47.3425681Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60913/answer","Biography information for Mr David Laws","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60913/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60913/answer",,,,,,,,,"60","Education","Education","2014-06-10","Free School Meals: North East","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, how much capacity funding for universal infant free school meals has been (a) requested by and (b) disbursed to schools in (i) Washington and Sunderland West constituency, (ii) the Sunderland local authority area and (iii) the North East region.","false","Biography information for Mrs Sharon Hodgson","Washington and Sunderland West","Mrs Sharon Hodgson","199863"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60914","Department for Education","false","2014-06-17","<p>We take into account an organisation's diversity policy and record where it is relevant to the subject matter of the contract or grant and is permissible by law. Where the organisation is listed as a Crown Strategic Supplier, we would also approach the relevant Crown Representative as part of the appraisal.</p><p> </p><p> </p>","South West Norfolk","Elizabeth Truss",,"2014-06-17T16:43:09.8288444Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60914/answer","Biography information for Elizabeth Truss","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60914/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60914/answer",,,,,,,,,"60","Education","Education","2014-06-10","Equality","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, what consideration his Department gives to the diversity policies and records of businesses or other organisations when considering their bid for commercial contracts or grants.","false","Biography information for Mrs Sharon Hodgson","Washington and Sunderland West","Mrs Sharon Hodgson","199946"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60915","Department for Education","false","2014-06-17","<p>Whilst the Department for Education does not set explicit targets for increasing diversity, Management Committee monitors representation rates on a monthly basis.</p><p>The table below shows the change to the workforce over the past year:</p><table><tbody><tr><td> </td><td> </td><td><p>May-13</p></td><td><p>May-14</p></td><td><p>Annual change (percentage points)</p></td></tr><tr><td rowspan="4"><p>Workforce</p></td><td><p>Black and minority ethnic</p></td><td><p>16.6%</p></td><td><p>16.6%</p></td><td><p>0.0</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Women</p></td><td><p>59.0%</p></td><td><p>57.8%</p></td><td><p>-1.2</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Disabled</p></td><td><p>11.7%</p></td><td><p>12.1%</p></td><td><p>+0.4</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>LGBT</p></td><td><p>4.0%</p></td><td><p>4.1%</p></td><td><p>+0.1</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><p>We also monitor the Department's representation rates at SCS against Civil Service 2013 targets:</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td> </td><td colspan="2"><p><strong>Female</strong></p></td><td colspan="2"><p><strong>BME</strong></p></td><td colspan="2"><p><strong>Disabled</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td> </td><td><p>DfE</p></td><td><p>CS target</p></td><td><p>DfE</p></td><td><p>CS target</p></td><td><p>DfE</p></td><td><p>CS target</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>SCS</p></td><td><p>44.1%</p></td><td><p>39%</p></td><td><p>5.4%</p></td><td><p>5%</p></td><td><p>5.7%</p></td><td><p>5%</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Women (Director and above)</p></td><td><p>42.9%</p></td><td><p>34%</p></td><td> </td><td> </td><td> </td><td> </td></tr></tbody></table>","South West Norfolk","Elizabeth Truss",,"2014-06-17T16:48:59.474617Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60915/answer","Biography information for Elizabeth Truss","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60915/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60915/answer",,,,,,,,,"60","Education","Education","2014-06-10","Equality","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, what targets his Department has for increasing diversity; and what progress has been made on meeting those targets in the last year.","false","Biography information for Mrs Sharon Hodgson","Washington and Sunderland West","Mrs Sharon Hodgson","199925"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60916","Department for Education","false","2014-06-17","<p>Our data does not record nationality; data held records only ethnicity.</p>","South West Norfolk","Elizabeth Truss",,"2014-06-17T16:44:09.1895086Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60916/answer","Biography information for Elizabeth Truss","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60916/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60916/answer",,,,,,,,,"60","Education","Education","2014-06-10","Disciplinary Proceedings","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, what proportion of staff within his Department who have been subject to formal disciplinary proceedings in each of the last five financial years classed themselves as white British.","false","Biography information for Mrs Sharon Hodgson","Washington and Sunderland West","Mrs Sharon Hodgson","199882"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60917","Department for Energy and Climate Change","false","2014-06-16","<p>From November 2010 a single team was established to control the process for all formal disciplinary proceedings being undertaken against Civil Servants in the Department of Energy &amp; Climate Change (DECC). Therefore central records only exist from that date.</p><p>The proportion of Civil Servants in DECC, who have been subject to formal disciplinary proceedings since November 2010 to date and who are white British, is less than 1% of the total number of Civil Servants in each year.</p><p> </p>","Bexhill and Battle","Gregory Barker",,"2014-06-16T11:58:31.909582Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60917/answer","Biography information for Lord Barker of Battle","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60917/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60917/answer",,,,,,,,,"63","Energy and Climate Change","Energy and Climate Change","2014-06-10","Disciplinary Proceedings","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Energy and Climate Change, what proportion of staff within his Department who have been subject to formal disciplinary proceedings in each of the last five financial years classed themselves as white British.","false","Biography information for Mrs Sharon Hodgson","Washington and Sunderland West","Mrs Sharon Hodgson","199883"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60918","Department for Energy and Climate Change","false","2014-06-16","<p>The Department currently works towards meeting the diversity representation targets set by the Cabinet Office for Senior Civil Servants. Our current rates against those targets are:</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><ul><li>Females in SCS – 34% (Target 39%)</li><li>Females at PB2 or above – 21% (Target 34%)</li><li>Disability – 3% (Target 5%)</li><li>Ethnicity – 1% (Target 5%)</li></ul><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","Bexhill and Battle","Gregory Barker",,"2014-06-16T11:57:52.1521469Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60918/answer","Biography information for Lord Barker of Battle","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60918/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60918/answer",,,,,,,,,"63","Energy and Climate Change","Energy and Climate Change","2014-06-10","Equal Opportunities","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Energy and Climate Change, what targets his Department has for increasing diversity; and what progress has been made on meeting those targets in the last year.","false","Biography information for Mrs Sharon Hodgson","Washington and Sunderland West","Mrs Sharon Hodgson","199926"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60919","Department for Energy and Climate Change","false","2014-06-16","<p>The Department of Energy and Climate Change considers diversity during the procurement or grant allocation process by including diversity within evaluation criteria when appropriate. Diversity is included when it is particularly relevant to the business requirements and circumstances of an individual procurement or grant. In addition the Department's standard terms and conditions of contract include specific clauses that cover equality and non-discrimination. The Department also promotes non-discrimination through open procurement procedures and we have removed barriers to supplier entry as part of our efforts to improve engagement with small and medium-sized enterprises. Our Contractors are required to abide by the DECC Equality Scheme, details of which can be found through the link below.</p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/47894/359-decc-equality-diversity-strategy-condoc.pdf" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/47894/359-decc-equality-diversity-strategy-condoc.pdf</a></p><p> </p>","Bexhill and Battle","Gregory Barker",,"2014-06-16T11:57:01.3551091Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60919/answer","Biography information for Lord Barker of Battle","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60919/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60919/answer",,,,,,,,,"63","Energy and Climate Change","Energy and Climate Change","2014-06-10","Equal Opportunities","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Energy and Climate Change, what consideration his Department gives to the diversity policies and records of businesses or other organisations when considering their bid for commercial contracts or grants.","false","Biography information for Mrs Sharon Hodgson","Washington and Sunderland West","Mrs Sharon Hodgson","199947"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60920","Department for Energy and Climate Change","false","2014-06-16","<p>From November 2010 a single team was established to control the process for all formal disciplinary proceedings being undertaken against Civil Servants in the Department of Energy &amp; Climate Change (DECC). Therefore central records only exist from that date.</p><p>The proportion of Civil Servants in DECC, who have been dismissed following formal disciplinary proceedings since November 2010 to date and who are white British, is less than 1% of the total number of Civil Servants in each year.</p><p> </p>","Bexhill and Battle","Gregory Barker",,"2014-06-16T11:56:20.7000817Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60920/answer","Biography information for Lord Barker of Battle","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60920/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60920/answer",,,,,,,,,"63","Energy and Climate Change","Energy and Climate Change","2014-06-10","Disciplinary Proceedings","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Energy and Climate Change, what proportion of staff within his Department who have been dismissed following formal disciplinary proceedings in each of the last five financial years classed themselves as white British.","false","Biography information for Mrs Sharon Hodgson","Washington and Sunderland West","Mrs Sharon Hodgson","199904"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60921","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2014-06-17","<p> </p><p>The data in the table relates to staff in core Defra only.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p>Financial year</p></td><td><p>Percentage of staff who have been dismissed following formal disciplinary proceedings who have not declared their ethnicity</p></td><td><p>Percentage of staff who have been dismissed following formal disciplinary proceedings who have declared themselves to be white British</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2009-10</p></td><td><p>No dismissals</p></td><td><p>No dismissals</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2010-11</p></td><td><p>No dismissals</p></td><td><p>No dismissals</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2011-12</p></td><td><p>100%</p></td><td><p>0%</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2012-13</p></td><td><p>No dismissals</p></td><td><p>No dismissals</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2013-14</p></td><td><p>No dismissals</p></td><td><p>No dismissals</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><p> </p><p>Employees declare their ethnicity and national identity on a voluntary basis.</p>","North Cornwall","Dan Rogerson",,"2014-06-17T14:41:58.1322747Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60921/answer","Biography information for Dan Rogerson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60921/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60921/answer",,,,,,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2014-06-10","Disciplinary Proceedings","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, what proportion of staff within his Department who have been dismissed following formal disciplinary proceedings in each of the last five financial years classed themselves as white British.","false","Biography information for Mrs Sharon Hodgson","Washington and Sunderland West","Mrs Sharon Hodgson","199905"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60922","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2014-06-16","<p> </p><p>Core Defra follows Cabinet Office advice in meeting its obligations under the Public Sector Equality Duty (PSED), which is part of the Equality Act 2010, when considering bids for commercial contracts or grants.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>As part of our evaluation criteria we ask each bidder to provide evidence of their equality and diversity policy or an equivalent document which demonstrates their organisation's commitment to equality and diversity and which is compliant with the relevant legislation.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>We ask each bidder to describe the steps they have taken to:</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>· monitor equality and diversity performance;</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>· implement training programmes for raising awareness;</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>· ensure staff and sub-contractors working on the contract comply appropriately with the relevant legislation;</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>· address cases of discrimination and other breaches and set out measures for preventing recurrences; and</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>· give the Department full confidence in their organisation's approach to equality and diversity.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>A score is allocated to the bidder's response to these questions which forms part of the overall technical evaluation of the bid.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","North Cornwall","Dan Rogerson",,"2014-06-16T14:53:32.300692Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60922/answer","Biography information for Dan Rogerson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60922/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60922/answer",,,,,,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2014-06-10","Equal Opportunities","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, what consideration his Department gives to the diversity policies and records of businesses or other organisations when considering their bid for commercial contracts or grants.","false","Biography information for Mrs Sharon Hodgson","Washington and Sunderland West","Mrs Sharon Hodgson","199948"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60923","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2014-06-17","<p> </p><p>The Civil Service has a longstanding commitment to promoting equality of opportunity and ensuring that the Civil Service is representative of the society it serves. Central to this is the principle of appointment on merit which is the foundation of Civil Service recruitment and enshrined in law.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>Core Defra does not have numerical targets for increasing our workforce diversity. However, Defra's Diversity and Inclusion Strategy 2013-15 contains a clear goal for Defra to become a diverse and inclusive Department ‘that can attract and retain talented people from the widest range of backgrounds and offer all our employees equality of opportunity to progress and achieve their potential on merit.'</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>Defra is also committed to reviewing our Equality Objectives and monitoring our performance against them and further information is provided in our Workforce Monitoring Report here:</p><p> </p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/organisations/department-for-environment-food-rural-affairs/about/equality-and-diversity" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/organisations/department-for-environment-food-rural-affairs/about/equality-and-diversity</a></p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>Defra's Diversity and Inclusion Strategy is underpinned by an action plan, with good progress made in the first year, including:</p><p> </p><ul><li>Mandating unconscious bias training for managers of people and those involved in recruitment and interviewing.</li><li>Introducing senior leader Diversity Champions for specific groups.</li><li>Participating fully in Positive Action Pathways, Diversity Schemes and Programmes.</li><li>Ongoing participation in the award winning ‘Summer Diversity Internship Programme', specifically aimed at underrepresented students.</li></ul><p> </p>","North Cornwall","Dan Rogerson",,"2014-06-17T16:45:08.8837724Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60923/answer","Biography information for Dan Rogerson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60923/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60923/answer",,,,,,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2014-06-10","Equality","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, what targets his Department has for increasing diversity; and what progress has been made on meeting those targets in the last year.","false","Biography information for Mrs Sharon Hodgson","Washington and Sunderland West","Mrs Sharon Hodgson","199927"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60924","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2014-06-17","<p> </p><p>The data in the table relates to staff in core Defra only.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p>Financial Year</p></td><td><p>Percentage of staff subject to formal disciplinary proceedings who have not declared their ethnicity</p></td><td><p>Percentage of staff subject to formal disciplinary proceedings who have declared themselves to be white British</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2009-10</p></td><td><p>33%</p></td><td><p>67%</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2010-11</p></td><td><p>75%</p></td><td><p>25%</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2011-12</p></td><td><p>33%</p></td><td><p>67%</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2012-13</p></td><td><p>17%</p></td><td><p>67%</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2013-14</p></td><td><p>25%</p></td><td><p>67%</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><p> </p><p>Employees declare their ethnicity and national identity on a voluntary basis.</p>","North Cornwall","Dan Rogerson",,"2014-06-17T14:45:15.4208916Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60924/answer","Biography information for Dan Rogerson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60924/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60924/answer",,,,,,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2014-06-10","Disciplinary Proceedings","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, what proportion of staff within his Department who have been subject to formal disciplinary proceedings in each of the last five financial years classed themselves as white British.","false","Biography information for Mrs Sharon Hodgson","Washington and Sunderland West","Mrs Sharon Hodgson","199884"
