"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60979","Department of Health","false","2014-06-17","<p>NHS England is responsible for the intellectual property strategy for the National Health Service.</p><p> </p><p>NHS England has advised that, as part of the Innovation Health and Wealth work programme, it has undertaken a review of the existing NHS intellectual property strategy and is revisiting this as part of its refresh of Innovation Health and Wealth which is currently being undertaken.</p><p> </p>","Central Suffolk and North Ipswich","Dr Daniel Poulter","200094 ; 200095 ; 200096 ; 200104 ; 200107","2014-06-17T14:58:25.0803239Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60979/answer","Biography information for Dr Dan Poulter","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60979/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60979/answer",,,,,,,,,"17","Health","Health","2014-06-10","NHS: Intellectual Property","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, who is responsible for the intellectual property policy of the NHS.","false","Biography information for Mr Virendra Sharma","Ealing, Southall","Mr Virendra Sharma","200098"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60980","Department of Health","false","2014-06-17","<p>The sunset review of all National Health Service/Department of Health funded innovation and improvement bodies, which formed part of the implementation plan for <em>Innovation Health and Wealth</em>, has been completed. Together with NHS England, we will be considering the approach to publication in due course.</p>","Central Suffolk and North Ipswich","Dr Daniel Poulter","200106","2014-06-17T15:02:21.143131Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60980/answer","Biography information for Dr Dan Poulter","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60980/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60980/answer",,,,,,,,,"17","Health","Health","2014-06-10","NHS: Innovation","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what evaluation was made of NHS innovation hubs by the Innovation, Health and Wealth sunset review.","false","Biography information for Mr Virendra Sharma","Ealing, Southall","Mr Virendra Sharma","200097"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60981","Department of Health","false","2014-06-17","<p>NHS England is responsible for the intellectual property strategy for the National Health Service.</p><p> </p><p>NHS England has advised that, as part of the Innovation Health and Wealth work programme, it has undertaken a review of the existing NHS intellectual property strategy and is revisiting this as part of its refresh of Innovation Health and Wealth which is currently being undertaken.</p><p> </p>","Central Suffolk and North Ipswich","Dr Daniel Poulter","200094 ; 200095 ; 200098 ; 200104 ; 200107","2014-06-17T14:58:25.7799082Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60981/answer","Biography information for Dr Dan Poulter","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60981/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60981/answer",,,,,,,,,"17","Health","Health","2014-06-10","NHS: Intellectual Property","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, how many commercial agreements were completed for the exploitation of NHS intellectual property by NHS organisations in each year from 2004 to 2010; and what total revenues to each such organisation was in each year from 2004 to 2010.","false","Biography information for Mr Virendra Sharma","Ealing, Southall","Mr Virendra Sharma","200096"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60982","Department of Health","false","2014-06-17","<p>NHS England is responsible for the intellectual property strategy for the National Health Service.</p><p> </p><p>NHS England has advised that, as part of the Innovation Health and Wealth work programme, it has undertaken a review of the existing NHS intellectual property strategy and is revisiting this as part of its refresh of Innovation Health and Wealth which is currently being undertaken.</p><p> </p>","Central Suffolk and North Ipswich","Dr Daniel Poulter","200095 ; 200096 ; 200098 ; 200104 ; 200107","2014-06-17T14:58:25.4240753Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60982/answer","Biography information for Dr Dan Poulter","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60982/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60982/answer",,,,,,,,,"17","Health","Health","2014-06-10","NHS: Intellectual Property","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what assessment he has made of the potential effect of the Commissioning for Quality and Innovation initiative on the commercialisation of intellectual property by NHS providers; and what metrics are used to monitor the commercialisation of such intellectual property.","false","Biography information for Mr Virendra Sharma","Ealing, Southall","Mr Virendra Sharma","200094"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60983","Department of Health","false","2014-06-17","<p>NHS England is responsible for the intellectual property strategy for the National Health Service.</p><p> </p><p>NHS England has advised that, as part of the Innovation Health and Wealth work programme, it has undertaken a review of the existing NHS intellectual property strategy and is revisiting this as part of its refresh of Innovation Health and Wealth which is currently being undertaken.</p><p> </p>","Central Suffolk and North Ipswich","Dr Daniel Poulter","200094 ; 200096 ; 200098 ; 200104 ; 200107","2014-06-17T14:58:25.7018243Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60983/answer","Biography information for Dr Dan Poulter","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60983/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60983/answer",,,,,,,,,"17","Health","Health","2014-06-10","NHS: Intellectual Property","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what Commissioning for Quality and Innovation payments have been made as a result of NHS providers complying with the commercialisation of intellectual property pre-qualification to date.","false","Biography information for Mr Virendra Sharma","Ealing, Southall","Mr Virendra Sharma","200095"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60984","Department of Health","false","2014-06-17","<p>NHS England is responsible for the intellectual property strategy for the National Health Service.</p><p> </p><p>NHS England has advised that, as part of the Innovation Health and Wealth work programme, it has undertaken a review of the existing NHS intellectual property strategy and is revisiting this as part of its refresh of Innovation Health and Wealth which is currently being undertaken.</p><p> </p>","Central Suffolk and North Ipswich","Dr Daniel Poulter","200094 ; 200095 ; 200096 ; 200098 ; 200107","2014-06-17T14:58:26.4361374Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60984/answer","Biography information for Dr Dan Poulter","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60984/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60984/answer",,,,,,,,,"17","Health","Health","2014-06-10","NHS: Intellectual Property","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, how many commercial deals were completed to exploit NHS intellectual property in each NHS organisation in each year from 2010 to date; and what revenue accrued to each NHS organisation from such deals in each year from 2010.","false","Biography information for Mr Virendra Sharma","Ealing, Southall","Mr Virendra Sharma","200104"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60985","Department of Health","false","2014-06-17","<p>My Rt hon Friend, the Secretary of State for Health, is under a legal obligation to keep NHS England's performance in achieving its objectives, as set out in the Mandate, under review. As part of this, he considers NHS England's compliance with its legal duties.</p><p> </p><p>NHS England has a statutory duty to promote innovation and clinical commissioning groups have a duty to promote innovation in the provision of health services in the exercise of their functions.</p><p> </p><p>The National Health Service's obligation to promote innovation is principally delivered through NHS England'sInnovation, Health and Wealth programme.</p><p> </p><p>NHS England has advised that monthly reports on the Innovation, Health and Wealth programme are made to the Department, the Prime Minister's Delivery Unit and the Innovation, Health and Wealth board.</p><p> </p>","Central Suffolk and North Ipswich","Dr Daniel Poulter","200099 ; 200100 ; 200102","2014-06-17T15:15:29.2188767Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60985/answer","Biography information for Dr Dan Poulter","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60985/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60985/answer",,,,,,,,,"17","Health","Health","2014-06-10","NHS: Innovation","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what steps he is taking to monitor the implementation of clinical commissioning groups' legal duty to promote innovation, adoption and diffusion of new techniques.","false","Biography information for Mr Virendra Sharma","Ealing, Southall","Mr Virendra Sharma","200105"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60986","Department of Health","false","2014-06-17","<p>The sunset review of all National Health Service/Department of Health funded innovation and improvement bodies, which formed part of the implementation plan for <em>Innovation Health and Wealth</em>, has been completed. Together with NHS England, we will be considering the approach to publication in due course.</p>","Central Suffolk and North Ipswich","Dr Daniel Poulter","200097","2014-06-17T15:02:21.2212918Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60986/answer","Biography information for Dr Dan Poulter","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60986/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60986/answer",,,,,,,,,"17","Health","Health","2014-06-10","NHS: Innovation","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, when the Innovation, Health and Wealth Sunset Review will be published.","false","Biography information for Mr Virendra Sharma","Ealing, Southall","Mr Virendra Sharma","200106"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60987","Department of Health","false","2014-06-17","<p>NHS England is responsible for the intellectual property strategy for the National Health Service.</p><p> </p><p>NHS England has advised that, as part of the Innovation Health and Wealth work programme, it has undertaken a review of the existing NHS intellectual property strategy and is revisiting this as part of its refresh of Innovation Health and Wealth which is currently being undertaken.</p><p> </p>","Central Suffolk and North Ipswich","Dr Daniel Poulter","200094 ; 200095 ; 200096 ; 200098 ; 200104","2014-06-17T14:58:26.5923858Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60987/answer","Biography information for Dr Dan Poulter","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60987/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60987/answer",,,,,,,,,"17","Health","Health","2014-06-10","NHS: Intellectual Property","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, how many innovations of each type have been identified and recorded in each year following the implementation of the Cquin pre-qualification of the commercialisation of intellectual property.","false","Biography information for Mr Virendra Sharma","Ealing, Southall","Mr Virendra Sharma","200107"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60988","Department of Health","false","2014-06-17","<p>My Rt hon Friend, the Secretary of State for Health, is under a legal obligation to keep NHS England's performance in achieving its objectives, as set out in the Mandate, under review. As part of this, he considers NHS England's compliance with its legal duties.</p><p> </p><p>NHS England has a statutory duty to promote innovation and clinical commissioning groups have a duty to promote innovation in the provision of health services in the exercise of their functions.</p><p> </p><p>The National Health Service's obligation to promote innovation is principally delivered through NHS England'sInnovation, Health and Wealth programme.</p><p> </p><p>NHS England has advised that monthly reports on the Innovation, Health and Wealth programme are made to the Department, the Prime Minister's Delivery Unit and the Innovation, Health and Wealth board.</p><p> </p>","Central Suffolk and North Ipswich","Dr Daniel Poulter","200099 ; 200100 ; 200105","2014-06-17T15:15:29.1563414Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60988/answer","Biography information for Dr Dan Poulter","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60988/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60988/answer",,,,,,,,,"17","Health","Health","2014-06-10","NHS: Innovation","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, who is responsible for auditing the compliance of clinical commissioning groups with their duty since the introduction of self-certification to provide innovation across all three stages of innovation.","false","Biography information for Mr Virendra Sharma","Ealing, Southall","Mr Virendra Sharma","200102"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60989","Department of Health","false","2014-06-17","<p>My Rt hon Friend, the Secretary of State for Health, is under a legal obligation to keep NHS England's performance in achieving its objectives, as set out in the Mandate, under review. As part of this, he considers NHS England's compliance with its legal duties.</p><p> </p><p>NHS England has a statutory duty to promote innovation and clinical commissioning groups have a duty to promote innovation in the provision of health services in the exercise of their functions.</p><p> </p><p>The National Health Service's obligation to promote innovation is principally delivered through NHS England'sInnovation, Health and Wealth programme.</p><p> </p><p>NHS England has advised that monthly reports on the Innovation, Health and Wealth programme are made to the Department, the Prime Minister's Delivery Unit and the Innovation, Health and Wealth board.</p><p> </p>","Central Suffolk and North Ipswich","Dr Daniel Poulter","200100 ; 200102 ; 200105","2014-06-17T15:15:28.5388757Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60989/answer","Biography information for Dr Dan Poulter","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60989/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60989/answer",,,,,,,,,"17","Health","Health","2014-06-10","NHS: Innovation","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, who is responsible for monitoring NHS England compliance with its duty to promote innovation across all three stages of innovation.","false","Biography information for Mr Virendra Sharma","Ealing, Southall","Mr Virendra Sharma","200099"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60990","Department of Health","false","2014-06-17","<p>My Rt hon Friend, the Secretary of State for Health, is under a legal obligation to keep NHS England's performance in achieving its objectives, as set out in the Mandate, under review. As part of this, he considers NHS England's compliance with its legal duties.</p><p> </p><p>NHS England has a statutory duty to promote innovation and clinical commissioning groups have a duty to promote innovation in the provision of health services in the exercise of their functions.</p><p> </p><p>The National Health Service's obligation to promote innovation is principally delivered through NHS England'sInnovation, Health and Wealth programme.</p><p> </p><p>NHS England has advised that monthly reports on the Innovation, Health and Wealth programme are made to the Department, the Prime Minister's Delivery Unit and the Innovation, Health and Wealth board.</p><p> </p>","Central Suffolk and North Ipswich","Dr Daniel Poulter","200099 ; 200102 ; 200105","2014-06-17T15:15:28.1299381Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60990/answer","Biography information for Dr Dan Poulter","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60990/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60990/answer",,,,,,,,,"17","Health","Health","2014-06-10","NHS: Innovation","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what metrics have been used to monitor NHS England's compliance with its duty to promote innovation across all three stages of innovation.","false","Biography information for Mr Virendra Sharma","Ealing, Southall","Mr Virendra Sharma","200100"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60991","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2014-06-17","<p /> <p /> <p>The Government has not produced forecasts of the number of children living in income poverty. The number of children in poverty is dependent on a number of factors which cannot be reliably predicted, including the median income.</p><p>The Government does not believe it is possible to accurately project child poverty to 2020. Poverty projections are rarely accurate. For example, IFS projections in October 2011 suggested the number of children in relative poverty would fall by 100,000 in 2010/11, whereas in fact it fell by 300,000.</p><p>Estimates of the number and proportion of children in relative and absolute low income are published in the National Statistics Households Below Average Income (HBAI) series. This information is captured using the Family Resources Survey (FRS) and has been reported since 1998/99; these estimates are available for each financial year up to 2011/12, the latest period for which estimates are available.</p><p>The estimates can be found at the link below:</p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/households-below-average-income-hbai-199495-to-201112" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/households-below-average-income-hbai-199495-to-201112</a> (ISBN 978-1-78153-531-8).</p><p>Relevant estimates can be found in Table 4.1tr - 4.4tr (on pages 102-5).</p>","Wirral West","Esther McVey",,"2014-06-17T16:08:32.6365632Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60991/answer","Biography information for Esther McVey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60991/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60991/answer",,,,,,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2014-06-10","Children: Poverty","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what the (a) forecast and (b) actual figures of (i) absolute and (ii) relative child poverty were in each year since the Child Poverty Act 2010 came into force.","false","Biography information for Chris Ruane","Vale of Clwyd","Chris Ruane","200109"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60992","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2014-06-16","<p> </p><p>Surveillance and monitoring has been carried out by the Forestry Commission and the Food and Environment Research Agency to provide intelligence on the rate of spread for Chalara. The surveillance in all four administrations is helping to determine the extent of the disease. This work will continue on new infected sites and, in consultation with stakeholders, the Government will consider what future surveillance work is needed.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>Further information on the management approach to Chalara and other established tree pests and pathogens in England can be found in the Tree Health Management Plan, which was published in April 2014.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/tree-health-management-plan" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/tree-health-management-plan</a></p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","North Cornwall","Dan Rogerson",,"2014-06-16T15:12:49.421297Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60992/answer","Biography information for Dan Rogerson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60992/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60992/answer",,,,,,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2014-06-10","Ash Dieback Disease","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, what recent assessment he has made of the state of health of the UK tree population following the recent Ash Dieback epidemic.","false","Biography information for Mr Gregory Campbell","East Londonderry","Mr Gregory Campbell","200115"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60993","Department for Energy and Climate Change","false","2014-06-16","<p>Ministers in the Department meet their ministerial counterparts from the Department of Energy in the United States of America on a number of occasions and have wide-ranging discussions.</p><p>All meetings between external organisations and Ministers in the Department of Energy and Climate Change are published on a quarterly basis on the Department's website and are available for download at this link:</p><p><a href="http://www.decc.gov.uk/en/content/cms/accesstoinform/registers/registers.aspx" target="_blank">http://www.decc.gov.uk/en/content/cms/accesstoinform/registers/registers.aspx</a></p><p>As has been the case with successive Administrations, it is not the Government's practice to provide details of all such meetings.</p><p> </p>","Sevenoaks","Michael Fallon",,"2014-06-16T11:59:12.0644574Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60993/answer","Biography information for Sir Michael Fallon","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60993/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60993/answer",,,,,,,,,"63","Energy and Climate Change","Energy and Climate Change","2014-06-10","Fracking: USA","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Energy and Climate Change, whether he has had any discussions with his counterpart in the United States Department of Energy as to any change in the estimated levels of recoverable shale gas reserves which has occurred in the US since fracking began; what effect, if any, this might have on potential fracking in the UK; and how the emerging lessons of shale gas extraction in the US and elsewhere are applied in calculating and updating estimates of recoverable reserves in the UK.","false","Biography information for Mr Gregory Campbell","East Londonderry","Mr Gregory Campbell","200161"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60994","Home Office","false","2014-06-16","<p> </p><p>The Home Office has issued no such guidance.</p><p> </p>","Ashford","Damian Green",,"2014-06-16T15:29:32.2094331Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60994/answer","Biography information for Damian Green","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60994/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60994/answer",,,,,,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2014-06-10","Police: Demonstrations","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what guidance she has issued to police forces on ensuring constituency and flexibility in policing of parades and demonstrations ensuring the smooth flow of traffic and safety of participants, motorists and pedestrians.","false","Biography information for Mr Gregory Campbell","East Londonderry","Mr Gregory Campbell","200114"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60995","Cabinet Office","false","2014-06-17","<p>Charity accounting rules require disclosure of charity employees in each £10,000 income band over £60,000. Copies of registered charities' accounts are available for inspection on the Charity Commission's website.</p><p> </p>","Ruislip, Northwood and Pinner","Mr Nick Hurd",,"2014-06-17T10:45:27.0354323Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60995/answer","Biography information for Mr Nick Hurd","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60995/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60995/answer",,,,,,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2014-06-10","Charities: Directors","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, how many directors of national charities were in receipt of annual salaries, pensions and other payments in excess of £150,000 in 2012-13.","false","Biography information for Mr Gregory Campbell","East Londonderry","Mr Gregory Campbell","200118"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60996","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2014-06-18","<p>The published National Aims Report shows the number of Further Education and Skills enrolments on each Learning Aim title, 2005/06 to 2011/12. This report will be updated with final data for the 2012/13 academic year soon.</p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/284252/January2013_NationalAims2011_12.zip" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/284252/January2013_NationalAims2011_12.zip</a></p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/statistical-data-sets/fe-data-library-further-education-and-skills" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/statistical-data-sets/fe-data-library-further-education-and-skills</a></p>","West Suffolk","Matthew Hancock",,"2014-06-18T15:18:05.4440017Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60996/answer","Biography information for Matt Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60996/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60996/answer",,,,,,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2014-06-10","Sign Language","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, how many people have begun learning British Sign Language in each of the last three years.","false","Biography information for Mr Gregory Campbell","East Londonderry","Mr Gregory Campbell","200117"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60997","Department of Health","false","2014-06-17","<p>On 22 May 2014, the European Medicines Agency's Committee for Medicinal Products for Human Use (CHMP) recommended granting a conditional marketing authorisation for Translarna (ataluren), an orphan designated medicine for the treatment of Duchenne muscular dystrophy caused by nonsense mutations. Translarna is to be used in patients aged five years and older who are able to walk.</p><p>The CHMP opinion on Translarna will now be sent to the European Commission for adoption of a decision on an European Union-wide marketing authorisation.</p><p>Other products are currently in various stages of development.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","North Norfolk","Norman Lamb",,"2014-06-17T16:35:00.7616691Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60997/answer","Biography information for Norman Lamb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60997/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60997/answer",,,,,,,,,"17","Health","Health","2014-06-10","Muscular Dystrophy","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what progress has been made in licensing drugs to deal with Duchenne muscular dystrophy.","false","Biography information for Mr Gregory Campbell","East Londonderry","Mr Gregory Campbell","200116"
