"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61092","HM Treasury","false","2014-06-12","<p>In January and February of this year, the government received two sets of follow up questions from the European Commission as part of their formal investigation into the Aggregates Levy Credit Scheme. Treasury officials worked closely with members of the industry and the authorities in Northern Ireland and have submitted further evidence in response to the questions posed.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p>Whilst a new relief scheme cannot be considered until the investigation concludes, the government remains fully committed to reinstating an aggregates levy credit scheme in Northern Ireland.</p>","Loughborough","Nicky Morgan",,"2014-06-12T15:06:34.798055Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61092/answer","Biography information for Nicky Morgan","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61092/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61092/answer",,,,,,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2014-06-10","Aggregates Levy: Northern Ireland","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what recent progress he has made on reinstating the Northern Ireland Aggregates Levy Credit Scheme.","false","Biography information for Baroness Ritchie of Downpatrick","South Down","Ms Margaret Ritchie","200110"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61093","Department of Health","false","2014-06-16","<p>Work is nearing completion to gain approvals to commence the procurement. The Department and Public Health England will start negotiations with Novartis, which produces the only licensed Meningitis B vaccine, as soon as possible.</p>","Battersea","Jane Ellison",,"2014-06-16T14:41:33.4967601Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61093/answer","Biography information for Jane Ellison","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61093/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61093/answer",,,,,,,,,"17","Health","Health","2014-06-10","Meningitis: Vaccination","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what progress has been made on procuring the vaccine for Meningitis B as part of the primary infant immunisation schedule; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Baroness Ritchie of Downpatrick","South Down","Ms Margaret Ritchie","199972"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61094","Home Office","false","2014-07-14","<p> </p><p>Her Majesty's Passport Office keeps staffing levels under review as part of <br>annual business planning.<br><br>We will consider long-term requirements in the light of the reviews which the <br>Home Secretary has commissioned on efficiency and forecasting.</p><p> </p>","Old Bexley and Sidcup","James Brokenshire",,"2014-07-14T16:17:18.9704616Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61094/answer","Biography information for James Brokenshire","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61094/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61094/answer",,,,,,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2014-06-10","HM Passport Office","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what her long-term plans are for staffing levels at HM Passport Office; and if she will make a statement.","false","Biography information for David Hanson","Delyn","Mr David Hanson","200101"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61095","Home Office","false","2014-06-30","<p> </p><p>The views of staff representatives are communicated to Ministers through the HM <br>Passport Office Chief Executive.<br>The Chief Executive holds regular fora and other meetings with staff at HM <br>Passport Office premises.<br>Events were held in:<br>Durham on 12 February 2014;<br>Liverpool on 14 March;<br>Southport on 30 April;<br>Belfast on 9 May; and<br>Newport on 16 May.<br><br>The Chief Executive also met local Public and Commercial Services union <br>representatives in those offices on those dates.</p><p> </p>","Old Bexley and Sidcup","James Brokenshire",,"2014-06-30T15:49:47.2390034Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61095/answer","Biography information for James Brokenshire","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61095/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61095/answer","Old Bexley and Sidcup","Old Bexley and Sidcup","James Brokenshire","James Brokenshire","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61095/answer/previousversion/1304","Biography information for James Brokenshire","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61095/answer/previousversion/1304","Biography information for James Brokenshire","1","Home Office","Home Office","2014-06-10","HM Passport Office","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, when (a) she, (b) Ministers in her Department and (c) the Chief Executive of HM Passport Office (HMPO) last met staff representatives of HMPO.","false","Biography information for David Hanson","Delyn","Mr David Hanson","200103"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61096","Home Office","false","2014-07-03","<p> </p><p> </p><p>A straightforward application is one where all the required information, <br>including supporting documentation, is provided, the application is signed, and <br>no further enquiries are required in order to progress the application.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","Old Bexley and Sidcup","James Brokenshire",,"2014-07-03T13:38:55.716511Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61096/answer","Biography information for James Brokenshire","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61096/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61096/answer",,,,,,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2014-06-10","Passports","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what her Department's definition of straightforward is in relation to passport applications.","false","Biography information for David Hanson","Delyn","Mr David Hanson","200157"
