"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61098","Home Office","false","2014-07-22","<p> </p><p> </p><p>The table below shows the number of Her Majesty's Passport Office full-time <br>equivalents working within the passport operational Directorates.<br>The formal record for workforce data is made on the last day of each calendar <br>month. We have therefore provided the data as of 31 March of each year.<br>(a) 2011- 2,586 <br>(b) 2012- 2,216<br>(c) 2013- 2,389<br>(d) 2014-2,593<br><br>Due to the limitations of the HR management system used prior to Dec 2010, it <br>is not possible to provide reliable management information below top level for <br>any periods prior to that date.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","Old Bexley and Sidcup","James Brokenshire",,"2014-07-22T14:43:47.140975Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61098/answer","Biography information for James Brokenshire","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61098/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61098/answer","Old Bexley and Sidcup","Old Bexley and Sidcup","James Brokenshire","James Brokenshire","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61098/answer/previousversion/1305","Biography information for James Brokenshire","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61098/answer/previousversion/1305","Biography information for James Brokenshire","1","Home Office","Home Office","2014-06-10","HM Passport Office","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, how many passport examining officers were employed by HM Passport Office in each year since 2010.","false","Biography information for David Hanson","Delyn","Mr David Hanson","200158"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61099","Home Office","false","2014-07-01","<p> </p><p>Her Majesty's Passport Ofice does not hold data on overtime payments in the format <br>requested. However, below is the overtime costs associated with additional work <br>undertaken in each month of 2014.<br><br><br>January - £199,146<br>February - £400,812<br>March - £840,588<br>April - £793,559<br>May - £964,742</p><p> </p>","Old Bexley and Sidcup","James Brokenshire",,"2014-07-01T13:35:18.196723Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61099/answer","Biography information for James Brokenshire","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61099/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61099/answer","Old Bexley and Sidcup","Old Bexley and Sidcup","James Brokenshire","James Brokenshire","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61099/answer/previousversion/1306","Biography information for James Brokenshire","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61099/answer/previousversion/1306","Biography information for James Brokenshire","1","Home Office","Home Office","2014-06-10","HM Passport Office","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, how much in additional payments has been paid to staff of HM Passport Office of each grade between po1 and 6 in each month of 2014; how many staff of each grade received such payments; and what the total amount of such payments is.","false","Biography information for David Hanson","Delyn","Mr David Hanson","200159"
